					<head>Midrash</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>Two fragments of Midrash ha-gadol, attributed to David Adani.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="261v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Midrash ha-gadol </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מדרש הגדול</title>
							<note>
								<p>Many marginal notes.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19572491">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19572491" xml:lang="en">Adani, David ben Amram </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/19572491" xml:lang="he">העדני, דוד בן עמרם </persName>
							</author>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="235v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Midrash ha-gadol</title>
								<note>
									<p>The main protion cotains the greater part of Midrash ha-gadol on Be-reshit.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="236r" to="261v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Midrash ha-gadol</title>
								<note>
									<p>Fragments of midrash on Va-yetse and Va-yishlaḥ.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of late 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>261 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>257</height>
										<width>190</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>195/215</height>
										<width>145/140</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>261 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each; many of the quires and separate leaves are missing. </p>
									<p>Signatures in Hebrew letters at the end of a quire. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several folios partly mutilted. </p>
									<p>Numerous folios missing. Imperfect at the beginning and at the end. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 2" ruledLines="27" writtenLines="27">
									<p>First part of the manuscript is divided to 2 columns, the latter part has pages undivided.  </p>
									<p>Many marginal (mostly lexical) notes. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Two Yemenite semi-cursive scripts of late 15th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="235v"/>and <locus from="236r" to="261v"/>- executed by two different but contemporary hands.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
